title: Chicago Northwest Hospitality EXPO 2019
description:
NEW LOCATION: MARRIOTT SCHAUMBURG
NEW DATE: MONDAY, NOV. 18
Planning a corporate event, meeting, luncheon, dinner, conference, retreat, outing or holiday party?  Please join the Daily Herald Business Ledger as a guest at the 2019 Chicago Northwest Hospitality EXPO.  The Chicago Northwest region has a wealth of facilities, resources and accommodations to meet any needs – large or small, business or personal.Visit with over 75 exhibitors with complimentary food and drinks from the best restaurants and venues in the area ... restaurants, hotels, breweries, country clubs, attractions, casinos, resorts, entertainment venues, caterers, sporting venues, conference centers, etc ... 
It's free to attend - registration required.Don't MISS the EXPO of the YEAR!
See you there ... 
Chris Craven, Director, 2019 Chicago Northwest Hospitality EXPO
 

TERMS OF ATTENDANCE
There is no charge to attend the Hospitality Expo. However, a valid e-mail address is required to register. By providing an e-mail address, attendee agrees to accept e-mails from participating exhibitors. You may opt out of these individual e-mails at any time.
Attendee agrees to fully indemnify and hold harmless Paddock Publications and the Daily Herald Business Ledger, its officers, employees and agents from any claim, demand, cause of action or suit in any way resulting from attendee’s use of the event premises, including all adjacent parking or other facilities.
No children, please. Must be 18 or older to attend.
EXHIBITORS 
The EXHIBITOR shall be liable and assume full responsibility for any damages to the event premises and its facilities as a result of careless or negligent behavior during the EXHIBITOR’S and its representative’s use of the event premises. The EXHIBITOR shall promptly repair or replace, at his or her own cost, any breakage, damage, or loss resulting from EXHIBITOR’S and its representative’s use of the property. The EXHIBITOR shall assume full responsibility for these costs including any attorney's fees incurred.
The EXHIBITOR shall be fully responsible for personal injury or property loss or damage resulting from EXHIBITOR’S use of the exhibition premises. The EXHIBITOR agrees to fully indemnify and hold harmless Paddock Publications and the Daily Herald Business Ledger, its officers, employees and agents from any claim, demand, cause of action or suit (including attorney's fees and all costs of investigation and defense) in any way resulting from Exhibitor’s use of the event premises, including all adjacent parking or other facilities.

title: Trinity Health Freedom Expo
description:
Trinity Health Freedom Expo is the premier, comprehensive natural and alternative health forum in the country, featuring two topical panels on essential oils and vaccines, dozens of educational lectures from experts and an exhibit hall to browse and shop.
 
You will encounter the newest products for consumers, practitioners and business owners; along with the latest technology such as state-of-the-art electronics, massage techniques, and cutting-edge modalities.  You will sample delicious, organic foods and you might even discover some must-have natural products for your home and the family.
 
What sets us apart from other health expos is that the information presented is not just about selling products to consumers. It’s about people with a passion for sharing information. We are all about empowering you to take control of your health so that you can teach others to do the same.
 
Expo Hours:
Saturday, 10/26 - 10:00am – 6:00pm
Sunday, 10/27 - 10:00am – 5:00pm

title: Illinois Institute of Technology (IIT) Real-Time Communications (RTC) Conference
description:
Illinois Institute of Technology (IIT) is pleased to announce the Real-TimeCommunications Lab will host the annual IIT Real-Time Communications (RTC) Conference and Expo – October 14 – 16, 2019 in Hermann Hall on the IIT main campus in Chicago, IL.
The IIT RTC Conference is a globally recognized collaborative event where the interactive multimedia and real-time communications industries and academia connect.
The conference  brings together developers, technical professionals and business executives from industry, standards, policy, regulatory, and research, promoting an open exchange of ideas to lead future development in the rapidly changing field of real-time communications
This year’s event promises to be the biggest and best to date! This is a multi-tracked conference that will run over three days, focusing on the major areas of:

Internet of Things (IoT)
WebRTC
Next Generation Emergency Communications
Programmable Telecom Networks
IPTComm – Juried research papers
TADSummit Americas

On Monday, October 14, registrants have the opportunity to participate in a day of Tutorials covering important and timely topics in real-time communications taught by leading subject-matter experts. Tutorials are complimentary for Full-conference registrants.
IPTComm, an independent academic conference whose focus is applied research in the area of Real-Time Communications, will once again be hosted as a track in the IIT RTC Conference. Research papers accepted by IPTComm will be presented in the track and published. Publication details will be available on the IPTComm website. The inclusion of the IPTComm conference offers our registrants, speakers, and sponsors the opportunity to attend two conferences in one, and builds on our unparalleled reputation for connecting industry thought leaders with academic researchers.
We’re excited to announce that the inaugural TAD Summit Americas will be co-located with IIT RTC Conference in 2019. For six years, Alan Quayle has produced TADSummit as the premier annual thought-leadership event in the programmable telecoms space. In 2019 TADSummit is expanding by hosting regional events in Asia, North America, and EMEA (Europe, Middle East and Africa).
By partnering with TADSummit Americas, IIT RTC Conference expands on its reputation for delivering the broadest range of unbiased real-time communications content in one amazing event.
The inclusion of TADSummit Americas and IPTComm offers our registrants, speakers, and sponsors the opportunity to attend three conferences in one, and builds on our unparalleled reputation for connecting industry thought leaders with academic researchers.
Please register to join us for these exciting events. In the meantime, stay tuned to our website and mailing lists for further updates or at:
IIT Twitter – LinkedIn – Facebook

title: Ramen Expo USA 2019
description:
RAMEN EXPO USA IS COMING TO CHICAGO!....and we're bringing some friends.... IZAKAYA EXPO USA
This is a B2B (Business-to-Business) event, with an opportunity for the public to gain access into the Japanese ramen industry.
Do you own a restaurant? Are you planning on opening a restaurant? Are you looking for authentic Japanese ingredients and products specializing in ramen for your restaurant? Or are you just curious about the Japanese ramen industry?  Come join us at the Donald E. Stephens Conventon Center in Rosemont, IL on October 6 & 7, 2019 (Sun & Mon) for Ramen Expo USA along with Izakaya Expo USA joining us for the first time this year!! Experience authentic Izakaya (Japanese Pub food) and of course, tons of delicious Ramen! 
This event is aimed to help build future business opportunities for ramen industry companies from Japan, by introducing them to those who are already established in the United States, and to others who are looking to start. Exhibitors in attendance will include Japanese food distributors, retailers, online shopping sites, Japanese ramen shops, noodle manufacturers, makers of gyoza, gyoza wrappers, sides, toppings, beverages, green tea, seasonings and sauces, manufactures of tableware, machine manufacturers, and many more! 
If you are involved with the restaurant/catering industry as a distributor, owner, purchaser, member of the media, or a food blogger, please register here for your opportunity to attend both days for free! Both days will open exclusively for registered Industry Pass holders at 11:00am. Then the doors will open at 1:00pm for general admission ticket holders. Both days will close at 4:00pm.
LIMITED TICKETS ARE AVAILABLE FOR GENERAL PUBLIC ADMISSION  SO GET YOURS TODAY!!!



GENERAL ADMISSION
DATES & TIME
There are two dates to choose from:
October 6, 2019 (Sun) – 1:00 pm to 4:00 pm 
1:00pm to 4:00pm – General Admission Tickets
October 7, 2019 (Mon) – 1:00 pm to 4:00 pm
 1:00pm to 4:00pm – General Admission Tickets


FAQs
Are there ID or minimum age requirements to enter the event?You must be 21+ to participate in alcohol tasting. Don't forget your ID!
Do I have to bring my printed pass to the event?Admission requires verification of your confirmation code/barcode which will be emailed to you upon registration. You can bring your phone/device showing this code, or bring a printout, whichever you prefer. 
Are cameras or video recorders allowed into the event?Yes! Photography and videos are encouraged. Please be sure to use #RamenExpoUSA on your social media posts.
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?For event related inquiries: jlatorre.ramenexpousa@gmail.com
For more info about the organizer: info@japaneseproductsproduce.com

ACE 2019 will showcase over 140 artists with one-of-a-kind pieces and museum-quality artwork. A highly competitive juried show, ACE features hand-crafted work in 12 media – baskets, ceramics, fiber decorative, fiber wearable, furniture, glass, jewelry, leather, metal, mixed media, paper and wood.

Proceeds from ACE benefit increased access to mental health services at NorthShore University HealthSystem. These critical funds are raised through Benefit Preview Party tickets, general admission tickets, sponsorships and our voluntary Craft for a Cause program. ACE does not receive a portion of proceeds from artist sales.

title: SPCS Young Professionals Conference: Chicago 2019
description:
We are excited to announce the 2nd Annual Young Professionals Networking Conference on Aug 23rd-25th, 2019 hosted in Downtown Chicago.
Registration is open through now through Aug 16th, 2019, please register. Space is limited!
The SPCS community is filled with knowledgeable, experienced, and driven members who can help young professionals reach their ambitious career goals. Through this networking conference, attendees will have the opportunity to build a robust professional network while also reinforcing the cultural connections that link us together.
Just as the SPCS Conventions have helped you meet new friends and connect with old, the SPCS Young Professionals Conference will help attendees meet new people to build their network in our community.
This conference will cater to those 21-35 years of age. Our goal is to create a strong professional and social network through the SPCS.
Location: Aloft Chicago Mag Mile
The registration fee is inclusive of:

2 night hotel stay at the Aloft hotel including taxes (not including incidentals) - Note: you will be paired with one other person randomly to room with unless otherwise specified during registration
Food for 3 day conference
Group activity on Saturday afternoon

If you have any questions, please contract us using the contact organizer form.
If you would to register without hotel room, please contact us using the contact organizer form.

title: Socialism 2019
description:
No Borders, No Bosses, No Binaries
In a moment of rising class struggle, resurgent social movements, and the growing popular appeal of socialism, the Socialism 2019 Conference will be an important gathering space for today’s left.
We're excited to announce that this year the conference will be sponsored by Haymarket Books and Jacobin. We hope that the conference will continue to bring together hundreds of activists from across the country for four days of organizing, learning, and collaboration.
Featuring dozens of panels, lectures, meet-ups, and workshops on topics like the fight against racism, how to win gender justice, radical working-class struggle, current debates on the left, and more, the Socialism Conference is an important contribution to the new socialist moment.
For information on speakers, schedules, and logistics, visit the Socialism Conference website.

title: TECHSPO Chicago 2019 Technology Expo (Internet ~ Mobile ~ AdTech ~ MarTech ~ SaaS)
description:
About TECHSPO Chicago 2019
WHERE BUSINESS, TECH AND INNOVATION COLLIDE IN CHICAGO!

TECHSPO Chicago is a 2-day technology expo taking place June 20 – 21, 2019 at the luxurious Hyatt Regency McCormick Place in Chicago, Illinois. TECHSPO Chicago brings together developers, brands, marketers, technology providers, designers, innovators and evangelists looking to set the pace in our advanced world of technology.
Exhibitors showcase the next generation of technology & innovation; including; Internet, Mobile, AdTech, MarTech & SaaS. Be prepared to be inspired, amazed and educated on how these evolving technologies will impact your business for the better.
As part of TECHSPO Chicago is a limited attendance paid event, DigiMarCon Midwest 2019 Digital Marketing Conference (https://digimarconmidwest.com). If the conference is where the learning, theory and inspiration happens, then the TECHSPO floor is where the testing, networking and product interaction takes place. 
Attendance is limited, Register today!

Venue
Hyatt Regency McCormick Place
2233 S Martin Luther King Dr, Chicago, IL 60616, United States



Step into the Hyatt Regency McCormick Place, where great things happen seamlessly. Conveniently connected to the McCormick Place Convention Center, this downtown Chicago hotel offers the ideal destination for you to work, relax and explore.  Enjoy the beautiful Lake Michigan backdrop and easy access to waterfront trails. Walk just outside of our doors to discover exciting Chicago attractions, like Soldier Field, Museum Campus, Millennium Park, and shopping on the Magnificent Mile. Hyatt Regency McCormick Place is a premier conference center venue where TECHSPO Chicago 2019 will be held.





TECHSPO Chicago 2019 will be held in the Regency Ballroom on the 2nd Floor.

title: TD Ameritrade presents Advanced Concepts Workshop - Chicago
description:
Description



Expand your investing know-how and become a more confident investor when you enroll in this free two-day educational workshop. You’ll gain unique insights and learn practical investing strategies from our experienced coaching team.

During this event you will:

Evaluate advanced options strategies against your personal financial goals
Discover strategies for different types of market conditions and learn how to consider high volatility market events as potential opportunities
Learn how to analyze options strategies using a probability-based approach
Hands-on experience using the award-winning thinkorswim® trading platform



Workshop Agenda



June 14th - 8:30 AM - 5:00 PM
Focus: Understanding Options Greeks, Volatility, and Calendar Spreads

Beyond delta: understanding vega & volatility skew
How implied volatility affects options and positions and revisit vertical spreads
Get to know calendar spreads, including what differentiates them from other types of spreads, probabilities, risk profile and more
Considerations for a sample Calendar Spreads investing plan




June 15th - 8:30 AM - 5:00 PM
Focus: Understanding Diagonal Spreads, Iron Condors, and ongoing support resources

Get to know diagonal spreads, including what differentiates them from other types of spreads, probabilities, and risk profiles, as well as considerations for a sample Diagonal Spreads investing plan
Get to know iron condors, choosing possible time frames and strike prices using a sample Iron Condors investing plan
Learn the main resources at TD Ameritrade to help you continue learning and refine your investing knowledge


Once you have your ticket, here's how you can prepare:

Bring your laptop to learn interactively during the workshop's hands-on instruction
Identify goals you want to accomplish in your workshop
Arrive early to get a good seat
Workshop rooms can be chilly—be sure to dress accordingly




All investing involves risks, including loss of principal.
Options are not suitable for all investors as the special risks inherent to option trading may expose investors to potentially rapid and substantial losses. Option trading privileges subject to TD Ameritrade review and approval. Please read Characteristics and Risks of Standardized Options.

Spreads and other multiple-leg option strategies can entail substantial transaction costs, including multiple commissions, which may impact any potential return. These are advanced option strategies and often involve greater risk, and more complex risk, than basic options trades.

title: OUT OF SIGHT Chicago 2019 Orientation
description:
Thank you for joining in on a summer of self-discovery and empowerment through OUT OF SIGHT this Summer!
 
We look forward to working with you to create meaningful experiences for participants, across all ages and dedicated teen camps in neighborhoods throughout Chicago.


Last year, Chicago welcomed Lawrence Weiner’s OUT OF SIGHT, a participatory floor installation (modeled after a hopscotch) that invites active participation and encourages audiences to consider the direction of their lives. This project was inspired by the concepts: 
 
Exuberance   Energy   Happiness   Vision   Visualization   
Enlightenment   Spontaneity   Serendipity 

In 2019 large scale installations of the marelle (French for hopscotch) are open to the public at the following parks:

Eugene Field Park  (Albany Park)
Hamilton Park Cultural Center (Engelwood)
Julia de Burgos Park (Humboldt Park/Logan Square)
La Villita Park (Little Village/South Lawndale)
Maggie Daley Park (the Loop)
Ping Tom Memorial Park (Chinatown) 

We welcome you to participate in the OUT OF SIGHT Chicago 2019 Orientation as we build our summer together. You will have the opportunity to:


Meet the OUT OF SIGHT team and learn more about the vision
Park Supervisors discuss their communities and the teen camper interests
Teaching Artists sharing their talents and build out weekly activities
Motivational Edge Miami's founders speak about creating OUT OF SIGHT programming for youth

We are thrilled to have you joining in on this year of discovery and play. Please RSVP by this Saturday, June 8th.

Hours are Saturday 10am-4pm and Sunday 10am-4pm. A single day pass works for either day of the event. For more event information, click here.

The Nourished Festivals (Formerly GFAF Expos) are the greatest events on earth for those living a gluten-free, allergen-friendly or special diet lifestyle. Sample and purchase hundreds of products, meet with brands, receive coupons and attend educational classes with industry experts. The Festivals have five zones to visit: Gluten-Free, Nut-Free, Paleo, Keto & Plant-Based. All products in all zones are gluten free. The Festivals are a fun, family-friendly, educational and safe place made just for you!

What do you get with your Festival Ticket?

Entry into the vendor fair with 100+ exhibiting brands
Coupons from the best gluten-free & allergen-friendly brands
Free samples from exhibitors- baked goods, gooey pizza, crunchy snacks & refreshing healthy options
Discounted products available for purchase
Informative classes related to the special diet lifestyle 
Free reusable bag to carry your goodies
The chance to meet your favorite brands, restaurants, authors & bloggers


*All sales are final. No refunds. Strollers, carts or wagons are allowed only for transporting children or medical equipment.

Presented by Enjoy Life Foods.

title: Bellavita Chicago 2019 - The Italian F&B Show | VIP Judge Pass
description:
Running for the fourth year in a row, Bellavita Expo takes place at the National Restaurant Association Show, Lakeside Center, May 18-21.
Visit Bellavita to discover a wide range of Italian food and beverages and apply here to vote for the best product of the show!
VIP Judges can decide to visit the Bellavita Italian pavilion on any day and at any time within the following judging opening times:


SATURDAY, MAY 18  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


SUNDAY, MAY 19  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


MONDAY, MAY 20  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.



As a VIP Judge, you will get to taste authentic Italian delicacies, connect with a whole new group of suppliers, and award those exhibitors who have earned the top spot.
Did you know? Bellavita VIP Judges have priority seating for all the cooking demos, wine tastings and industry panels at the Bellavita Food & Wine Academy! Click here to see the full schedule.
Professionals eligible to attend the National Restaurant Association Show may obtain a Bellavita VIP Judge pass. We reserve the right to amend this list based on the criteria required to attend the trade show. Specifically, attendance will not be granted to anyone who does not clearly state their job role within the F&B industry.
All the F&B professionals who will make the selection process can get free entry for the 2019 National Restaurant Association Show upon request. The result of your application will be emailed to you before May 18.To learn more, contact Bellavita Awards Director Enrico Longobucco at elongobucco@quirismedia.com

title: 68th BetterInvesting National Convention
description:
BetterInvesting's National Convention offers dozens of sessions on selecting stocks and other investments, planning for retirement, managing a portfolio and more. Investors of all experience levels can find sessions to meet their interests, from the basics of investing in stocks to discussions of investment clubs, exchange-traded funds, dividend stocks, and options. Panel discussions on stock selection round out the event — attendees are sure to come away with several investment ideas to study.
Your full registration includes:
Thursday Evening Welcome Reception and Opening Bell Ceremony
Full schedule of 60 Educational Classes on Friday, Saturday and Sunday
Friday Evening Exhibitor Reception and Stock Selection Panel
Classes, Door Prizes and Closing Bell Ceremony on Sunday till noon
 
List of Classes
 
BINC FAQs
Due to the tremendous response, Chicago Marriott is SOLD OUT. OVERFLOW HOTEL – the same room rate of $129 (if available) SpringHill Suites by Marriott Chicago O’Hare, a few blocks from the convention hotel There will be a shuttle to transport guests to & from the BINC hotel. Register at BetterInvesting National Convention Overflow webpage
 
Make your hotel reservation for BINC early!!!! The National Restaurant Association is holding their 100th Centennial Show during the same time as BINC. Over 65,000 people will be attending this show and hotel rooms will be in short supply. You are encouraged to make your hotel reservation now as the hotel is filling up fast.  Remember you are able to cancel your hotel reservation up to 6:00 pm on the night of your arrival at no charge and any deposit will be fully refunded.
 
BINC Registration Cancellation Policy: Cancellations MUST be received in writing by April 1, 2019. All cancellations are subject to a $50 fee. NO refunds will be made after April 1, 2019.

title: "Who Do You Say That I Am?" Why the Humanity of Jesus Matters
description:
"Who Do You Say That I Am?"  Why the Humanity of Jesus Matters
April 4-5, 2019
Our existence is a bodily existence.  Because we experience the world and one another through our bodies, a first principle of historic Christianity has been that, in order that God may redeem all of our existence, Jesus assumed our humanity in its fullness. 
Yet, in our discussions about Jesus’s person and work, and our relationship with the triune God, Christians have sometimes presented Christianity as a religion concerned exclusively with the afterlife, neglecting the importance of present realities. 
In this conference we invite you to explore with us why the humanity of Jesus is central to the Christian understanding of salvation. Over the span of two days we will explore how the reality of the Incarnation challenges and redeems our broken social structures, including racial and ethnic divisions, economic systems, and sexuality.
*Plenary Address by Fleming Rutledge will be free and open to the public. 
Speakers:
Fleming Rutledge, Author, Theologian, Episcopal Priest
Lynn Cohick, Denver Seminary
Darrell Bock, Dallas Theological Seminary
Brian E. Daley, S.J., University of Notre Dame
Robin Jensen, University of Notre Dame
Dana Harris, Trinity Evangelical Divinity School
Esau McCaulley, Northeastern Seminary
Scot McKnight, Northern Seminary
Christopher Hays, Fundación Universitaria Seminario Biblico de Colombia
Milton Acosta, Fundación Universitaria Seminario Biblico de Colombia
David Hooker, Wheaton College
George Kalantzis, Wheaton College
David Capes, Wheaton College

Questions? Contact theology.conference@wheaton.edu.

title: TD Ameritrade presents Technical Analysis & Options Strategies Workshop - Chicago
description:
Expand your investing know-how and become a more confident investor when you enroll in this free two-day educational workshop. You’ll gain unique insights and learn practical investing strategies from our experienced coaching team. 
 
During this event you will learn:

Strategies designed to generate income and enhance returns
Strategies for protecting a portfolio against loss in times of market volatility
The basics of stock charting, price patterns, and Fibonacci retracements
Ways to create your own rules for a trading strategy that meets your needs


Workshop Agenda
February 15 - 8:30 AM - 5:00 PM
Understanding Trends, Support & Resistance, and Candlestick Patterns

Go beyond highs and lows and learn to see like a technician
Interpret bullish and bearish candlestick patterns
Identify potential technical entry and exit signals
Create your own rules for a trading strategy that meets your needs

February 16 - 8:30 AM - 5:00 PM
Understanding Options Basics, Covered Calls, Cash-Secured Puts, and Verticals

Understand options terminology and discover the options greeks
Explore covered calls and cash-secured puts
Consider short vertical spreads and ideas on choosing time frames and strike prices
Create your own rules for a trading strategy that meets your needs


Once you have your ticket, here's how you can prepare:

Bring your laptop to learn interactively during the workshop's hands-on instruction
Identify goals you want to accomplish in your workshop
Arrive early to get a good seat
Workshop rooms can be chilly—be sure to dress accordingly

 
 



All investing involves risks, including loss of principal. 
The presentations are provided for general information purposes only and should not be considered individualized recommendations or advice.
Options are not suitable for all investors as the special risks inherent to option trading may expose investors to potentially rapid and substantial losses. Option trading privileges subject to TD Ameritrade review and approval. Please read Characteristics and Risks of Standardized Options.
Spreads and other multiple-leg option strategies can entail substantial transaction costs, including multiple commissions, which may impact any potential return.  These are advanced option strategies and often involve greater risk, and more complex risk, than basic options trades.
Supporting documentation for any claims, comparison, statistics, or other technical data will be supplied upon request.
While this workshop discusses technical analysis, other approaches, including fundamental analysis, may assert very different views.
